PN,41202
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F412A1771920251
OL,3,CLovejoy episode helps antiques dealer
OL,4,Cspot plaques stolen from Napoleon III
OL,5,Ctomb
OL,7,FBut now, Hampshire Constabulary has
OL,8,Fbeen able to return two of the plaques
OL,9,Fafter receiving a call from Derbyshire-
OL,10,Fbased antiques dealer Paul Gostelow.
OL,12,FA spokesman for the force said Mr
OL,13,FGostelow had recognised that they
OL,14,Fdated back to the Napoleonic era after
OL,15,Fspotting a motif which he had seen on
OL,16,Fan episode of the BBC comedy-drama
OL,17,FLovejoy, which featured Ian McShane as
OL,18,Fan antiques dealer.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/7
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,413,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41203
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F412A1771920251
OL,3,CLovejoy episode helps antiques dealer
OL,4,Cspot plaques stolen from Napoleon III
OL,5,Ctomb
OL,7,FThe spokesman said: "In February 2014
OL,8,Fthe Crypt of Napoleon Bonaparte III,
OL,9,Flast Emperor of France, was burgled
OL,10,Fand three unique, historically
OL,11,Fimportant and priceless altar plaques
OL,12,Fwere taken.
OL,14,F"After 12 years they were thought to
OL,15,Fhave been lost, until a chance call to
OL,16,Fthe constabulary on 10 February this
OL,17,Fyear from an antiques dealer in
OL,18,FDerbyshire ` Paul Gostelow ` who said
OL,19,Fhe had two of the stolen plaques.
OL,26,@oD@UOUvD@AOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/7
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,413,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41204
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F412A1771920251
OL,3,CLovejoy episode helps antiques dealer
OL,4,Cspot plaques stolen from Napoleon III
OL,5,Ctomb
OL,7,F"Remarkably, Paul knew them to be from
OL,8,Fthe Napoleonic era due to the ball and
OL,9,Fcrown in the corner of the frame `
OL,10,Fwhich he recognised from an episode of
OL,11,Fthe 90s Brit TV series Lovejoy.
OL,13,F"The call to police was intercepted by
OL,14,FPc Mark Webb from the Country Watch
OL,15,FRural Crime Task Force, who is our
OL,16,Fheritage crime specialist.
OL,18,F"Some investigation with the
OL,19,FInternational Stolen Arts Register
OL,20,Fconfirmed that they were indeed the
OL,21,Fitems.
OL,26,@oD@AOUuD@AOUzD@AOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/7
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,413,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41205
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F412A1771920251
OL,3,CLovejoy episode helps antiques dealer
OL,4,Cspot plaques stolen from Napoleon III
OL,5,Ctomb
OL,7,F"Officers from the task force last
OL,8,Fweek travelled to Derbyshire to
OL,9,Frecover the items, and Pc Webb was
OL,10,Fable to return them to St Michael's
OL,11,FAbbey in Farnborough for restoration
OL,12,Fand return to their place in the
OL,13,Fcrypt."
OL,15,FThe spokesman added: "Ongoing work has
OL,16,Fidentified a number of lines of
OL,17,Finquiry and efforts will be made to
OL,18,Flocate the third plaque, which remains
OL,19,Fmissing."
OL,26,@oD@AOUuD@GO]
